A clearing and forwarding agent, Festus Alumina, who allegedly defrauded a man of N1.7 million under false pretence, on Thursday, appeared at an Ebute Meta Chief Magistrates’ Court in Lagos. Alumina, 44, who is to face trial on charges bordering on false pretence, fraud and stealing, has entered a “not guilty” plea. However, the Police Prosecutor, Insp Cousin Adams, insisted that the defendant committed the offences sometimes in September and October 2018 at Apapa, Tin can Area, Lagos. Adams said that the defendant had collected the sum of N1.7 million from Olatunji Adekunle, the complainant, under the pretext that he would help him clear some goods. The defendant had assured the complainant that he would help him clear his 1×40 ft container and a Honda Accord 2012 model, but had failed in his promise, he alleged. The alleged offences violated Sections 287, 314 and 411 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. The Chief Magistrate, Mr Alex Komolafe, admitted the defendant to bail in the sum of N100,000 with two sureties each in like sum. The court fixed June 6 for further hearing. (NAN)